The Italian treasury said it would offer3,500 billion lire of short-term treasury bills (BOTs) at ratesslightly lower than the preceding offer in mid-February.    It said it would offer 1,500 billion lire of six-monthpaper priced at 95.35 pct for a net annualised compound yieldof 9.30 pct. Net yield on the preceding issue was 9.46 pct.    The treasury said it would also offer 2,000 billion lire of12-month bills at a base price of 91.15 pct for a net annualyield of 9.05 pct, down from 9.22 pct in mid-February.    The bills replace maturing paper worth 3,196 billion lireand subscriptions to the offer close March 10. REUTER&#3;